1
00:01:35,900 --> 00:01:38,300
[Too Young To Love]

2
00:01:38,620 --> 00:01:41,100
[Episode 4]

3
00:01:54,200 --> 00:01:56,400
How's your cello practice
been going lately?

4
00:01:56,400 --> 00:01:57,280
It's okay.

5
00:01:57,280 --> 00:01:58,680
"Okay" isn't good enough.

6
00:01:58,680 --> 00:01:59,940
You need to be the best.

7
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:01,200
Only by getting first place

8
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:02,680
will people remember you.

9
00:02:02,680 --> 00:02:03,410
Understand?

10
00:02:04,100 --> 00:02:04,480
Mm.

11
00:02:06,560 --> 00:02:07,200
Ning...

12
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:12,200
Never mind, nothing.

13
00:02:12,470 --> 00:02:13,470
Go on practicing.

14
00:02:26,710 --> 00:02:27,590
Let's go, Lan!

15
00:03:09,120 --> 00:03:10,430
I'm so envious.

16
00:03:11,240 --> 00:03:12,120
If only I could

17
00:03:12,120 --> 00:03:14,680
bring my own cello to perform.

18
00:03:16,710 --> 00:03:18,280
Just borrow one from them later.

19
00:03:18,280 --> 00:03:19,940
They shouldn't be that petty.

20
00:03:20,280 --> 00:03:20,960
Then you can go up

21
00:03:20,960 --> 00:03:21,840
and play with them.

22
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:22,680
No way.

23
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:24,840
Instruments are
precious personal belongings.

24
00:03:24,840 --> 00:03:26,360
We don't lend them out lightly.

25
00:03:26,360 --> 00:03:27,000
Forget it.

26
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:28,000
I'll just listen.

27
00:03:44,520 --> 00:03:45,000
Sir,

28
00:03:45,240 --> 00:03:46,150
excuse me.

29
00:03:46,680 --> 00:03:48,010
That girl over there...

30
00:03:49,280 --> 00:03:49,710
I...

31
00:03:49,960 --> 00:03:51,220
I'll go get the coffee.

32
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:55,000
Thanks.

33
00:03:55,560 --> 00:03:56,079
Come on.

34
00:03:56,520 --> 00:03:57,680
M... Me?

35
00:03:57,840 --> 00:03:58,360
Come on.

36
00:03:58,360 --> 00:03:58,870
Can I?

37
00:04:03,960 --> 00:04:04,710
Thank you.

38
00:04:07,520 --> 00:04:08,450
You've got this.

39
00:04:09,840 --> 00:04:11,840
What piece do you want to play, miss?

40
00:04:12,310 --> 00:04:13,590
The Concerto for Two Cellos?

41
00:04:13,590 --> 00:04:14,590
Of course.

42
00:04:15,750 --> 00:04:17,920
Aren't you usually the levelheaded one?

43
00:04:17,920 --> 00:04:20,040
Why didn't you explain it clearly
to our daughter?

44
00:04:20,040 --> 00:04:21,160
Don't you know what kind of temper

45
00:04:21,160 --> 00:04:22,420
your own daughter has?

46
00:04:22,870 --> 00:04:23,720
She's just like you—
proud and high-spirited

47
00:04:23,720 --> 00:04:24,720
since childhood.

48
00:04:25,360 --> 00:04:25,750
Now

49
00:04:25,920 --> 00:04:27,250
you're going to tell her

50
00:04:27,390 --> 00:04:29,160
the company went bankrupt
and we're in debt?

51
00:04:29,160 --> 00:04:30,960
You want me to just tell her that?

52
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:33,159
Fine.

53
00:04:34,920 --> 00:04:37,120
Studying abroad is a major step in life.

54
00:04:37,510 --> 00:04:38,720
Before Ning goes abroad,

55
00:04:38,720 --> 00:04:40,320
I'll have the tuition ready.

56
00:04:41,190 --> 00:04:42,240
No matter what,

57
00:04:42,720 --> 00:04:44,520
Ning's future can't be delayed.

58
00:04:44,720 --> 00:04:45,950
She is our only daughter

59
00:04:45,950 --> 00:04:47,360
and all our hope.

60
00:04:48,270 --> 00:04:49,040
She must attend

61
00:04:49,040 --> 00:04:51,370
the best music conservatory in the world!

62
00:06:23,120 --> 00:06:30,220
[Reborn! We Got This]

63
00:06:32,159 --> 00:06:33,159
That was amazing.

64
00:06:35,750 --> 00:06:36,750
I have a call.

65
00:06:37,510 --> 00:06:38,070
Hello?

66
00:06:39,600 --> 00:06:40,190
Ning.

67
00:06:40,190 --> 00:06:41,510
I just saw the video Mengmeng

68
00:06:41,510 --> 00:06:42,920
shared in the group chat.

69
00:06:43,070 --> 00:06:44,190
You looked quite happy

70
00:06:44,190 --> 00:06:45,360
playing the cello.

71
00:06:47,390 --> 00:06:48,390
What's wrong?

72
00:06:48,390 --> 00:06:50,510
Your voice sounds a little strange.

73
00:06:51,510 --> 00:06:52,360
It's nothing.

74
00:06:53,950 --> 00:06:55,390
You can tell me, you know.

75
00:06:55,630 --> 00:06:56,750
In the future, if you're unhappy,

76
00:06:56,750 --> 00:06:58,150
you can always talk to me.

77
00:06:58,480 --> 00:07:00,270
I'll keep all your secrets.

78
00:07:02,830 --> 00:07:03,950
Then let me ask you—

79
00:07:04,720 --> 00:07:06,160
if one day

80
00:07:06,270 --> 00:07:07,070
you face

81
00:07:07,070 --> 00:07:08,160
a huge setback,

82
00:07:08,160 --> 00:07:09,160
what would you do?

83
00:07:12,830 --> 00:07:15,040
A huge setback...

84
00:07:17,270 --> 00:07:18,950
I once read that

85
00:07:19,630 --> 00:07:20,720
if fate

86
00:07:21,270 --> 00:07:22,190
wants to give you

87
00:07:22,190 --> 00:07:23,590
a really wonderful gift,

88
00:07:24,040 --> 00:07:25,970
it will first push you to the brink—

89
00:07:27,070 --> 00:07:29,600
so you'll be strong enough to catch it.

90
00:07:30,190 --> 00:07:31,510
When things hit rock bottom,
they turn around—

91
00:07:31,510 --> 00:07:33,570
every dark night ends at dawn, right?

92
00:07:34,630 --> 00:07:35,600
The brink...

93
00:07:41,830 --> 00:07:43,920
If that gift really exists,

94
00:07:44,480 --> 00:07:45,830
I hope that one day

95
00:07:46,720 --> 00:07:48,830
I'll play the cello on the greatest stage

96
00:07:48,830 --> 00:07:49,720
in the world.

97
00:07:55,510 --> 00:07:56,390
Me too.

98
00:07:58,270 --> 00:07:59,360
Right now,

99
00:08:00,070 --> 00:08:01,600
I'm 100% sure

100
00:08:02,510 --> 00:08:04,170
that I love playing the cello.

101
00:08:05,950 --> 00:08:06,830
Then let's

102
00:08:07,070 --> 00:08:08,160
never give up.

103
00:08:09,160 --> 00:08:09,890
Let's always

104
00:08:10,190 --> 00:08:11,850
love playing the cello, okay?

105
00:08:12,070 --> 00:08:12,600
Okay.

106
00:08:13,070 --> 00:08:14,000
I believe in you.

107
00:08:15,950 --> 00:08:16,550
Thank you.

108
00:08:24,340 --> 00:08:27,220
["International Cello Program";
Study Abroad with Scholarship]

109
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:36,030
One floor,

110
00:08:36,360 --> 00:08:37,150
two floors,

111
00:08:37,150 --> 00:08:37,960
three floors.

112
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:40,000
How big is it altogether?

113
00:08:40,150 --> 00:08:41,390
I've never thought about it.

114
00:08:41,390 --> 00:08:43,360
Maybe two or three thousand square meters.

115
00:08:43,360 --> 00:08:44,480
That big?

116
00:08:44,870 --> 00:08:47,360
You even have a private elevator and pool.

117
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:49,860
It's all thanks to my parents' hard work.

118
00:08:49,960 --> 00:08:51,720
I wish I had parents like yours.

119
00:08:51,720 --> 00:08:52,600
Me too!

120
00:08:52,600 --> 00:08:53,870
Me too!

121
00:08:54,320 --> 00:08:55,360
No way.

122
00:08:59,360 --> 00:09:00,290
I'm telling you,

123
00:09:00,320 --> 00:09:02,120
the hardest part of a barbecue

124
00:09:02,120 --> 00:09:03,200
is getting the fire started.

125
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:04,400
But I have already...

126
00:09:04,600 --> 00:09:05,480
got it started.

127
00:09:05,480 --> 00:09:06,720
Amazing, so amazing.

128
00:09:06,720 --> 00:09:08,080
So when can we eat?

129
00:09:08,320 --> 00:09:08,840
Relax.

130
00:09:08,840 --> 00:09:10,570
It needs to burn a while longer.

131
00:09:14,870 --> 00:09:16,360
Tong Xiaole, stop filming.

132
00:09:16,360 --> 00:09:17,550
Come help set up!

133
00:09:18,480 --> 00:09:19,010
I'm busy.

134
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:26,720
Alright,

135
00:09:26,720 --> 00:09:27,720
the fire is ready!

136
00:09:27,720 --> 00:09:28,180
Xiaole,

137
00:09:28,440 --> 00:09:29,870
bring the oil and skewers over.

138
00:09:29,870 --> 00:09:31,080
I'm about to start grilling them.

139
00:09:31,080 --> 00:09:31,480
Okay.

140
00:09:31,670 --> 00:09:32,360
The oil...

141
00:09:32,360 --> 00:09:33,960
For that, we've gotta ask
Tong Xiaole to do it.

142
00:09:33,960 --> 00:09:35,840
He lies through his teeth all the time.

143
00:09:35,840 --> 00:09:37,970
He's basically a walking greaseball.

144
00:09:39,840 --> 00:09:41,370
What's wrong, greaseball?

145
00:09:48,480 --> 00:09:49,410
Where's the oil?

146
00:09:50,200 --> 00:09:51,600
Isn't the oil right here?

147
00:09:55,720 --> 00:09:57,670
Are you sure
you've got the grilling covered,

148
00:09:57,670 --> 00:09:58,200
Mr. Chen?

149
00:09:59,120 --> 00:10:00,480
Leave it to me.

150
00:10:03,550 --> 00:10:04,080
Mr. Chen,

151
00:10:04,080 --> 00:10:05,720
your villa is great and all,

152
00:10:05,720 --> 00:10:07,080
except that the temperature difference

153
00:10:07,080 --> 00:10:07,960
between day and night is too huge.

154
00:10:07,960 --> 00:10:09,290
You're being picky now?

155
00:10:14,960 --> 00:10:16,420
Chen Fan, do you need help?

156
00:10:16,840 --> 00:10:18,360
Sure. Help me grab

157
00:10:18,840 --> 00:10:20,370
the mushrooms on the table.

158
00:10:20,440 --> 00:10:22,080
I picked them from the hill
behind our house.

159
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:23,200
I love mushrooms.

160
00:10:23,480 --> 00:10:25,080
Picked from the back hill...

161
00:10:25,080 --> 00:10:26,940
They're not poisonous, are they?

162
00:10:27,720 --> 00:10:28,550
Let me see.

163
00:10:31,870 --> 00:10:32,840
Do you remember

164
00:10:32,840 --> 00:10:34,080
my dad teaching us

165
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:36,080
how to

166
00:10:36,360 --> 00:10:38,490
identify mushrooms when we were kids?

167
00:10:38,790 --> 00:10:39,600
This kind...

168
00:10:39,870 --> 00:10:41,840
should be edible, right?

169
00:10:42,840 --> 00:10:44,200
I don't remember.

170
00:10:44,790 --> 00:10:45,920
It should be edible!

171
00:10:48,120 --> 00:10:48,720
Should be shiitake.

172
00:10:48,720 --> 00:10:49,320
That's right.

173
00:10:49,320 --> 00:10:50,200
Just eat without worry.

174
00:10:50,200 --> 00:10:52,360
Then I'm going to pig out later.

175
00:10:53,840 --> 00:10:55,720
Help me grill the mushrooms.

176
00:10:55,960 --> 00:10:56,480
Okay.

177
00:10:56,960 --> 00:10:58,080
These are done, right?

178
00:10:58,080 --> 00:10:58,960
Yes, yes, yes.

179
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:02,480
Coming.

180
00:11:03,840 --> 00:11:04,840
I'm starving.

181
00:11:04,840 --> 00:11:05,720
Everyone, grab a few skewers.

182
00:11:05,720 --> 00:11:06,600
Thank you.

183
00:11:08,240 --> 00:11:09,480
Thank you.

184
00:11:18,720 --> 00:11:19,240
Not bad skills,

185
00:11:19,240 --> 00:11:19,840
Mr. Chen.

186
00:11:24,080 --> 00:11:25,550
Here you go!

187
00:11:26,790 --> 00:11:27,670
Smells so good!

188
00:11:34,080 --> 00:11:34,600
Yi Lan,

189
00:11:34,870 --> 00:11:36,080
don't you like mushrooms?

190
00:11:36,080 --> 00:11:36,840
There's mushroom soup here.

191
00:11:36,840 --> 00:11:37,480
Have some?

192
00:11:37,600 --> 00:11:38,200
Okay.

193
00:11:38,360 --> 00:11:39,240
Is it ready?

194
00:11:39,790 --> 00:11:40,870
Ready.

195
00:11:41,720 --> 00:11:42,670
Thanks.

196
00:11:48,360 --> 00:11:49,200
Here.

197
00:11:52,840 --> 00:11:53,360
Here.

198
00:11:53,550 --> 00:11:54,670
Thanks.

199
00:11:55,360 --> 00:11:56,560
Have some mushrooms.

200
00:11:56,870 --> 00:11:58,870
Mushrooms taste best when grilled.

201
00:12:06,360 --> 00:12:07,820
Wild mushrooms really are

202
00:12:08,080 --> 00:12:09,010
something else.

203
00:12:16,360 --> 00:12:18,630
If only there were stars in the sky.

204
00:12:24,600 --> 00:12:25,550
It's raining.

205
00:12:25,790 --> 00:12:26,870
No way.

206
00:12:34,790 --> 00:12:36,960
Which idiot picked this "perfect" day?

207
00:12:36,960 --> 00:12:37,840
Unbelievable.

208
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:38,320
You picked it!

209
00:12:38,320 --> 00:12:38,790
You did!

210
00:12:38,790 --> 00:12:39,240
You did!

211
00:12:39,240 --> 00:12:39,790
You did!

212
00:12:39,790 --> 00:12:40,320
You did!

213
00:12:40,320 --> 00:12:41,080
Whoever picked it is an idiot!

214
00:12:41,080 --> 00:12:41,840
I picked it.

215
00:12:47,240 --> 00:12:50,000
Well, I think rainy days are kind of nice.

216
00:12:57,750 --> 00:12:58,480
What else

217
00:12:58,480 --> 00:13:00,480
can we do on a rainy day?

218
00:13:02,120 --> 00:13:03,200
I'm going to shower first.

219
00:13:03,200 --> 00:13:04,400
Don't fight me for it!

220
00:13:06,120 --> 00:13:07,980
The barbecue was soaked through.

221
00:13:08,120 --> 00:13:08,790
I'll go check

222
00:13:08,790 --> 00:13:10,590
if there's anything else to eat.

223
00:13:19,360 --> 00:13:20,960
I'm going to charge my phone.

224
00:13:56,600 --> 00:13:58,130
He took so many photos of me.

225
00:14:05,600 --> 00:14:06,670
You took all those photos of me

226
00:14:06,670 --> 00:14:08,330
and won't even let me see them?

227
00:14:08,790 --> 00:14:10,590
Didn't the battery die just now?

228
00:14:13,870 --> 00:14:14,600
Give it to me.

229
00:14:14,600 --> 00:14:16,360
I haven't picked a profile picture yet.

230
00:14:16,360 --> 00:14:17,870
Didn't you come up to find food?

231
00:14:17,870 --> 00:14:18,800
Did you find any?

232
00:14:18,840 --> 00:14:19,480
Not yet.

233
00:14:19,960 --> 00:14:21,000
Then let me see the photos first!

234
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:23,730
I remember Chen Fan's place
has some down here...

235
00:14:29,600 --> 00:14:30,660
There's food here!

236
00:14:30,870 --> 00:14:31,550
Let me see!

237
00:14:31,550 --> 00:14:32,000
Look over there!

238
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:32,660
There's...

239
00:14:38,200 --> 00:14:39,390
W-Why did it go dark?

240
00:14:40,670 --> 00:14:41,800
Did the power go out?

241
00:14:43,360 --> 00:14:44,480
The power's out?

242
00:14:47,200 --> 00:14:47,840
Where is Mengmeng?

243
00:14:47,840 --> 00:14:48,440
Mengmeng!

244
00:14:48,600 --> 00:14:49,200
Lan!

245
00:14:49,200 --> 00:14:49,800
Mengmeng!

246
00:14:50,080 --> 00:14:51,200
Lan, Lan,

247
00:14:51,200 --> 00:14:52,670
I'm scared to be alone,

248
00:14:52,670 --> 00:14:53,240
Lan!

249
00:14:53,240 --> 00:14:54,320
You grabbed the wrong person.

250
00:14:54,320 --> 00:14:55,200
I'm here.

251
00:14:55,200 --> 00:14:56,080
Lan.

252
00:14:56,870 --> 00:14:58,080
I'm scared too.

253
00:14:58,200 --> 00:14:58,960
What should we do now?

254
00:14:58,960 --> 00:14:59,820
How about this—

255
00:14:59,960 --> 00:15:00,960
you two wait here.

256
00:15:01,550 --> 00:15:02,810
I'll go down and check.

257
00:15:03,240 --> 00:15:04,480
Don't go! Don't go!

258
00:15:04,480 --> 00:15:05,440
Xiaole!

259
00:15:06,600 --> 00:15:08,730
Then... let's slowly feel our way out.

260
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:16,320
Why is it so dark?

261
00:15:18,240 --> 00:15:19,640
Probably a power outage.

262
00:15:21,150 --> 00:15:22,320
Why is it raining?

263
00:15:22,870 --> 00:15:24,870
Wasn't it already raining just now?

264
00:15:25,080 --> 00:15:26,080
I'm so dizzy!

265
00:15:26,080 --> 00:15:26,720
It's the lightning.

266
00:15:26,720 --> 00:15:28,780
Thunder and rain are totally normal.

267
00:15:29,960 --> 00:15:31,240
The Water Curtain Cave.

268
00:15:31,240 --> 00:15:32,600
Water Curtain Cave!

269
00:15:37,840 --> 00:15:38,790
There's a horse!

270
00:15:39,790 --> 00:15:40,390
It's fake.

271
00:15:40,480 --> 00:15:41,120
Horse.

272
00:15:42,120 --> 00:15:43,480
Horse.

273
00:15:43,510 --> 00:15:44,120
Horse.

274
00:15:44,360 --> 00:15:45,690
Stop imagining things.

275
00:15:45,720 --> 00:15:47,720
We live in a scientific world, okay?

276
00:15:47,720 --> 00:15:49,440
Stick to materialism, alright?

277
00:15:49,440 --> 00:15:50,240
Materialism.

278
00:15:53,320 --> 00:15:54,630
Who? Who did that?

279
00:15:55,120 --> 00:15:55,670
Chen Fan,

280
00:15:55,670 --> 00:15:56,790
can you not pop out like that?

281
00:15:56,790 --> 00:15:57,720
You scared us half to death!

282
00:15:57,720 --> 00:15:59,030
Chen Fan!

283
00:15:59,440 --> 00:16:01,480
I'm scared to be alone.

284
00:16:01,480 --> 00:16:02,740
Let's stick together.

285
00:16:04,240 --> 00:16:06,120
W-What's wrong?

286
00:16:06,120 --> 00:16:07,870
It looked like a figure over there!

287
00:16:07,870 --> 00:16:08,670
There was a figure?

288
00:16:08,670 --> 00:16:09,600
Where?

289
00:16:09,600 --> 00:16:10,240
Bro,

290
00:16:10,240 --> 00:16:12,440
that's your face-shaped sofa!

291
00:16:13,240 --> 00:16:14,200
Unbelievable.

292
00:16:14,360 --> 00:16:16,090
Where is your circuit breaker?

293
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:17,670
By the door.

294
00:16:17,670 --> 00:16:18,720
Go flip the switch, hurry.

295
00:16:18,720 --> 00:16:19,480
You're brave.

296
00:16:19,480 --> 00:16:21,080
-You go!
-You go!

297
00:16:21,080 --> 00:16:22,320
Of course I can go!

298
00:16:22,320 --> 00:16:23,000
But if I go,

299
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:24,200
who will protect you?

300
00:16:24,360 --> 00:16:25,720
This is your house!

301
00:16:25,720 --> 00:16:26,650
You want me to go?

302
00:16:27,440 --> 00:16:28,170
Don't worry!

303
00:16:28,200 --> 00:16:29,200
I'll protect you!

304
00:16:29,870 --> 00:16:30,840
Let's do this—

305
00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:32,480
Yi Lan, you on my left,

306
00:16:32,550 --> 00:16:33,480
and Qiao Mengmeng, you on my right.

307
00:16:33,480 --> 00:16:34,940
I-I'll stand on your left.

308
00:16:36,870 --> 00:16:38,240
Let's go together.

309
00:16:38,240 --> 00:16:39,200
Wait a second!

310
00:16:39,440 --> 00:16:41,840
Isn't this formation just protecting you?

311
00:16:43,480 --> 00:16:44,440
I figured

312
00:16:44,440 --> 00:16:45,840
if anything happens to any of you,

313
00:16:45,840 --> 00:16:47,000
I can rush to your rescue

314
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:48,080
immediately!

315
00:16:48,360 --> 00:16:49,480
Coward!

316
00:16:49,480 --> 00:16:51,080
Alright!

317
00:16:51,080 --> 00:16:52,440
Let's move!

318
00:16:52,440 --> 00:16:53,080
Let's go!

319
00:16:56,670 --> 00:16:57,470
Open the door.

320
00:16:57,670 --> 00:16:58,060
Open the door.

321
00:16:58,060 --> 00:16:58,530
Open the door.

322
00:16:58,530 --> 00:16:59,330
Open the door.

323
00:17:09,829 --> 00:17:12,480
I still haven't achieved my dreams!

324
00:17:12,480 --> 00:17:13,589
I'm too young to die!

325
00:17:13,589 --> 00:17:14,829
Help!

326
00:17:22,240 --> 00:17:23,240
It sounds like someone's knocking.

327
00:17:23,240 --> 00:17:24,440
Go check it out!

328
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:26,030
It's a person knocking!

329
00:17:26,030 --> 00:17:27,069
A person knocking!

330
00:17:27,069 --> 00:17:28,160
Knocking on the door!

331
00:17:28,160 --> 00:17:30,070
Only humans can knock on something, right?

332
00:17:30,070 --> 00:17:31,240
You go!

333
00:17:31,240 --> 00:17:32,350
Come on, let's go!

334
00:17:32,350 --> 00:17:33,110
If I go,

335
00:17:33,110 --> 00:17:34,310
who will protect you?

336
00:17:34,920 --> 00:17:35,920
Hurry up! Come on!

337
00:17:39,830 --> 00:17:40,440
Hurry!

338
00:17:43,790 --> 00:17:45,240
I don't want to!

339
00:17:47,310 --> 00:17:48,110
Wait!

340
00:17:51,550 --> 00:17:52,310
You go!

341
00:17:52,310 --> 00:17:53,160
Y-You go!

342
00:17:53,160 --> 00:17:54,020
Hurry up and go!

343
00:17:58,270 --> 00:17:59,000
I'm going then.

344
00:17:59,000 --> 00:17:59,440
Go.

345
00:18:14,830 --> 00:18:16,110
Y-You can do it.

346
00:18:30,510 --> 00:18:32,110
See? No one's there!

347
00:18:37,110 --> 00:18:38,350
I'm Zhao Zhenghao!

348
00:18:39,030 --> 00:18:40,360
It's me, Zhao Zhenghao!

349
00:18:40,440 --> 00:18:41,350
Zhao Zhenghao?

350
00:18:41,830 --> 00:18:43,440
Xiaole! Xiaole!

351
00:18:44,270 --> 00:18:45,270
Well, I think he's

352
00:18:45,270 --> 00:18:46,440
Zhao Zhenghao!

353
00:18:49,440 --> 00:18:50,400
Zhao Zhenghao?

354
00:18:50,680 --> 00:18:51,550
Zhao Zhenghao?

355
00:19:05,200 --> 00:19:06,330
Finally warming up.

356
00:19:08,160 --> 00:19:08,920
Xiaole.

357
00:19:09,240 --> 00:19:10,960
You hit me way too hard.

358
00:19:11,680 --> 00:19:12,680
Sorry about that.

359
00:19:13,000 --> 00:19:15,350
I trained at the Shaolin Temple as a kid.

360
00:19:15,350 --> 00:19:16,070
That was

361
00:19:16,070 --> 00:19:18,000
pure muscle memory.

362
00:19:18,750 --> 00:19:20,920
Then let's settle this man to man.

363
00:19:21,310 --> 00:19:22,400
Alright, that's enough.

364
00:19:22,400 --> 00:19:23,880
Don't ask for trouble.

365
00:19:24,920 --> 00:19:26,320
Tell us, why did you come?

366
00:19:29,590 --> 00:19:30,590
I invited him.

367
00:19:31,880 --> 00:19:33,310
I think you guys

368
00:19:33,310 --> 00:19:35,790
might have had a tiny misunderstanding.

369
00:19:36,550 --> 00:19:39,030
Well, Zhao Zhenghao is pretty handsome.

370
00:19:39,030 --> 00:19:41,760
You can take this chance to
get to know him better.

371
00:19:43,240 --> 00:19:44,240
To find you guys...

372
00:19:44,240 --> 00:19:45,510
Look at this heavy rain.

373
00:19:45,510 --> 00:19:47,270
I risked my life to come here.

374
00:19:47,750 --> 00:19:49,510
Shouldn't you welcome me?

375
00:19:52,790 --> 00:19:54,270
We're hungry and sleepy.

376
00:19:54,270 --> 00:19:55,530
How can we welcome you?

377
00:19:56,030 --> 00:19:57,110
I'm hungry too.

378
00:19:57,110 --> 00:19:59,040
I haven't eaten anything tonight.

379
00:20:00,750 --> 00:20:01,920
Where are you going?

380
00:20:05,030 --> 00:20:06,070
Zhao Zhenghao!

381
00:20:06,070 --> 00:20:06,920
The barbecue outside

382
00:20:06,920 --> 00:20:08,320
is all soaked by the rain.

383
00:20:08,350 --> 00:20:09,680
We can't eat it anymore!

384
00:20:18,510 --> 00:20:20,070
Look, let's share.

385
00:20:20,160 --> 00:20:21,890
Zhao Zhenghao, you're so nice.

386
00:20:22,110 --> 00:20:23,240
In such heavy rain,

387
00:20:23,270 --> 00:20:25,240
you still came all this way to find us.

388
00:20:25,240 --> 00:20:26,550
Zhao Zhenghao, I didn't expect

389
00:20:26,550 --> 00:20:28,150
you to be such a loyal friend.

390
00:20:28,310 --> 00:20:30,160
How did I not notice before?

391
00:20:30,160 --> 00:20:31,030
Exactly.

392
00:20:31,030 --> 00:20:33,160
Zhao Zhenghao, you're handsome and loyal.

393
00:20:33,160 --> 00:20:34,550
We should get to know him better.

394
00:20:34,550 --> 00:20:36,000
You might not know me well.

395
00:20:36,000 --> 00:20:37,200
I'm a really nice guy.

396
00:20:38,160 --> 00:20:40,560
We can start getting to
know each other now.

397
00:20:43,640 --> 00:20:44,640
I feel so sleepy.

398
00:20:44,920 --> 00:20:45,720
What?

399
00:20:46,030 --> 00:20:47,960
I just got here, and you're sleepy?

400
00:20:48,350 --> 00:20:49,350
Get up and party!

401
00:20:52,830 --> 00:20:53,830
I've got to hand it to you.

402
00:20:53,830 --> 00:20:54,920
After coming all this way,

403
00:20:54,920 --> 00:20:56,920
how do you still have so much energy?

404
00:20:57,590 --> 00:20:58,310
Do you think

405
00:20:59,110 --> 00:21:00,550
the mushrooms we just ate

406
00:21:00,680 --> 00:21:01,830
are okay?

407
00:21:04,550 --> 00:21:06,010
You said they were edible.

408
00:21:06,070 --> 00:21:07,880
I told you they were poisonous.

409
00:21:11,790 --> 00:21:13,790
Hear me well:

410
00:21:14,070 --> 00:21:15,400
to prevent

411
00:21:15,640 --> 00:21:17,070
any further accidents,

412
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:18,750
I suggest

413
00:21:19,070 --> 00:21:20,830
that we go to sleep right now.

414
00:21:23,640 --> 00:21:24,440
Hello, Dad.

415
00:21:25,350 --> 00:21:27,110
I ate something bad last night.

416
00:21:27,270 --> 00:21:28,070
What did you eat?

417
00:21:28,070 --> 00:21:28,880
Mushrooms.

418
00:21:29,070 --> 00:21:30,510
How could you be so careless?

419
00:21:30,510 --> 00:21:31,720
I ate the most.

420
00:21:31,920 --> 00:21:32,980
What are you doing?

421
00:21:33,830 --> 00:21:35,000
Xiaole is here!

422
00:21:35,200 --> 00:21:35,680
Look.

423
00:21:36,110 --> 00:21:36,680
Hello, Uncle Dong.

424
00:21:36,680 --> 00:21:37,350
Hello, Xiaole.

425
00:21:37,350 --> 00:21:38,070
We're all together.

426
00:21:38,070 --> 00:21:39,070
Don't worry.

427
00:21:39,640 --> 00:21:41,110
It's beautiful here.

428
00:21:41,590 --> 00:21:42,240
Look.

429
00:21:42,830 --> 00:21:44,230
The environment is nice.

430
00:21:45,070 --> 00:21:46,600
The weather is great today.

431
00:21:46,790 --> 00:21:47,750
Have fun then.

432
00:21:48,310 --> 00:21:49,370
What are you doing?

433
00:21:54,240 --> 00:21:55,550
Mom, I'm fine.

434
00:21:55,550 --> 00:21:56,350
I'm safe.

435
00:21:56,550 --> 00:21:57,350
Come back soon.

436
00:21:57,350 --> 00:21:58,480
I'll be back very soon.

437
00:21:58,480 --> 00:21:59,070
Come on, come on!

438
00:21:59,070 --> 00:22:00,270
Breakfast is here!

439
00:22:00,720 --> 00:22:01,270
Xiaole,

440
00:22:01,350 --> 00:22:02,200
come on.

441
00:22:02,440 --> 00:22:03,030
Xiaole.

442
00:22:03,830 --> 00:22:04,750
Where is my son?

443
00:22:05,350 --> 00:22:07,200
Chen Fan? Chen Fan!

444
00:22:08,510 --> 00:22:10,680
Here! Coming!

445
00:22:10,880 --> 00:22:11,400
Come on!

446
00:22:11,400 --> 00:22:12,160
Breakfast is ready!

447
00:22:12,160 --> 00:22:14,510
Mom, Mom, Mom.

448
00:22:15,400 --> 00:22:17,550
Honestly, you kids...

449
00:22:17,550 --> 00:22:18,440
Why didn't you tell me sooner?

450
00:22:18,440 --> 00:22:20,240
I would've come over last night
if I'd known!

451
00:22:20,240 --> 00:22:21,310
Come on.

452
00:22:21,310 --> 00:22:23,270
Fan, have a fried dough stick.

453
00:22:26,400 --> 00:22:27,640
This is for you.

454
00:22:28,110 --> 00:22:29,270
Here, for you two.

455
00:22:29,790 --> 00:22:30,880
Thank you, Auntie.

456
00:22:33,590 --> 00:22:34,790
Who hasn't got one? Here.

457
00:22:34,790 --> 00:22:35,350
Stop talking.

458
00:22:35,350 --> 00:22:36,240
Just eat.

459
00:22:36,440 --> 00:22:37,640
You must be starving.

460
00:22:41,510 --> 00:22:43,440
There are more fried dough sticks.

461
00:22:44,070 --> 00:22:45,240
So sweet.

462
00:23:08,240 --> 00:23:09,270
Not happy?

463
00:23:10,680 --> 00:23:11,240
No.

464
00:23:11,790 --> 00:23:13,310
The last piece of nougat.

465
00:23:13,310 --> 00:23:15,040
I'll give it to you—make a wish.

466
00:23:19,350 --> 00:23:20,110
Thanks.

467
00:23:22,440 --> 00:23:23,350
Look!

468
00:23:23,590 --> 00:23:24,650
There's a rainbow!

469
00:23:24,830 --> 00:23:25,640
Look, look!

470
00:23:26,350 --> 00:23:27,160
Do you see it?

471
00:23:28,440 --> 00:23:29,270
Where?

472
00:23:29,830 --> 00:23:30,830
Only happy people

473
00:23:30,830 --> 00:23:32,110
can see it.

474
00:23:33,640 --> 00:23:34,640
No wonder then.

475
00:23:37,110 --> 00:23:37,830
Do you remember

476
00:23:37,830 --> 00:23:39,750
that song we sang in kindergarten,

477
00:23:39,750 --> 00:23:40,440
"Come On"?

478
00:23:40,790 --> 00:23:42,350
The song the teacher kept making you sing

479
00:23:42,350 --> 00:23:44,350
as punishment
for causing trouble in class?

480
00:23:44,350 --> 00:23:46,070
It was obviously you
who always pulled my pigtails

481
00:23:46,070 --> 00:23:47,470
and got punished to sing.

482
00:23:47,790 --> 00:23:49,030
Don't think that
just because you have good grades now,

483
00:23:49,030 --> 00:23:49,680
nobody remembers

484
00:23:49,680 --> 00:23:50,830
what you were like as a kid.

485
00:23:50,830 --> 00:23:51,830
Don't slander me.

486
00:23:51,830 --> 00:23:52,830
Talk is cheap.

487
00:23:52,830 --> 00:23:53,960
Where's your proof?

488
00:23:54,510 --> 00:23:56,030
Hello there. Come on.

489
00:23:56,030 --> 00:23:57,550
Wait for me!

490
00:23:58,070 --> 00:23:58,880
Happiness

491
00:23:58,880 --> 00:24:00,920
is waiting for everyone ahead!

492
00:24:00,920 --> 00:24:01,590
Let go of me!

493
00:24:01,590 --> 00:24:02,350
Hello there.

494
00:24:02,350 --> 00:24:03,240
Come on!

495
00:24:03,240 --> 00:24:04,400
This is so embarrassing!

496
00:24:04,400 --> 00:24:05,110
Let go of me!

497
00:24:05,790 --> 00:24:06,400
Don't run!

498
00:24:06,400 --> 00:24:08,060
Dance by yourself if you want!

499
00:24:09,590 --> 00:24:11,190
I'm feeling much better now.

500
00:24:12,270 --> 00:24:13,400
You really shouldn't

501
00:24:13,400 --> 00:24:15,600
participate in such activities again.

502
00:24:16,880 --> 00:24:17,880
If something like that happens again,

503
00:24:17,880 --> 00:24:19,160
call Dad immediately.

504
00:24:19,920 --> 00:24:21,750
Dad will come over right away

505
00:24:22,070 --> 00:24:22,590
to protect you.

506
00:24:22,590 --> 00:24:23,240
Alright, alright,

507
00:24:23,240 --> 00:24:24,100
that's enough.

508
00:24:24,270 --> 00:24:24,790
Lan,

509
00:24:24,790 --> 00:24:26,030
have some hot soup, quickly.

510
00:24:26,030 --> 00:24:26,680
Okay.

511
00:24:45,730 --> 00:24:46,000
[Home] [Explore] [Food]

512
00:24:46,170 --> 00:24:47,430
[Food]

513
00:24:47,670 --> 00:24:48,590
[Rou jia mo]

514
00:24:48,240 --> 00:24:49,240
Xiaole!

515
00:24:48,620 --> 00:24:49,100
[Food]

516
00:24:50,270 --> 00:24:51,640
Tong Xiaole, open the door!

517
00:24:51,640 --> 00:24:52,680
Coming!

518
00:24:57,400 --> 00:24:58,590
You must be starving!

519
00:24:58,590 --> 00:25:00,250
I brought you something good!

520
00:25:00,270 --> 00:25:00,920
Come in!

521
00:25:03,790 --> 00:25:04,510
Come on.

522
00:25:04,880 --> 00:25:06,750
Let me see what good food you brought.

523
00:25:06,750 --> 00:25:08,110
Braised chicken.

524
00:25:13,160 --> 00:25:14,070
It's still hot.

525
00:25:14,070 --> 00:25:15,070
Eat up.

526
00:25:15,070 --> 00:25:17,160
I'll put this container
in the fridge for you.

527
00:25:17,160 --> 00:25:17,440
Okay.

528
00:25:17,440 --> 00:25:19,640
Heat it up yourself when you're hungry.

529
00:25:30,310 --> 00:25:31,680
I peeled these.

530
00:25:34,030 --> 00:25:34,920
You're improving.
